text.section:
As used in KRS 117.055 to 117.0555 and KRS 117.0557, "establish a precinct" shall include the following:
Creating a new precinct;
Dividing one (1) precinct into two (2) or more precincts;
Combining two (2) or more precincts into one (1) precinct; and
Altering a boundary line between two (2) or more precincts.

The order prescribed in subsection (2) of this section shall include:
A written description of the boundaries of each precinct to be established;
A map or maps clearly showing the boundaries of each precinct to be established;
The estimated number of registered voters in each precinct to be established; and
Any additional information which may be required by an administrative regulation adopted by the State Board of Elections under KRS Chapter 13A for the purposes of assuring compliance with KRS 117.055 to 117.0555 and KRS 117.0557.
